                  (where he spent much of his time), Burton came to know <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> at Oxford. <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s first recorded letter
                  to him is dated <date when="1726-05-02">May 2, 1726</date>. From <date when="1731"
                     >1731</date> Burton was also vicar of <placeName>Buckland,
                     Berkshire</placeName>, where <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"
                     />JW</persName> occasionally preached for him. In <date when="1734">1734</date>
                  Burton became vicar of <placeName>Mapledurham, Oxfordshire</placeName>, where he
                  served until <date when="1766">1766</date>. In the mid <date>1730s</date> Burton
                  was a very active founding trustee of the colony of
                  <placeName>Georgia</placeName>, helping to underwrite the cost of a catechist
                  there. He recruited <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>
                  for the project and rejoiced in his acceptance. See <hi rend="italic">Alumni
                     Oxonienses</hi>; and <hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>.</p>
